A brief overview of the history of photography. Learning to choose the right numerical aperture, exposure time and focal length. Learning how to take into account natural light both outdoors and indoors, photo composition, focal points, perspective, etc. when taking photos. Practical courses include taking photos of detailed and general views. Learning the basic techniques of photo-processing and preparing photos for print.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To learn the principles of photography and how to take photos of satisfactory quality.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who have completed the course: - are familiar with the principles of photography and know how to take those principles into account in practice; - know how to use different photography settings on cameras; - are familiar with the aesthetic and technical possibilities of photo composition; - are familiar with the specifics of product photos and photos describing the work process; - know how to read and interpret information in photos and pick photos according to their informational properties and function; - are capable of taking photos of their works and work processes.
